---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Insurance for International Electricians | Compare Expat Plans";
const description = "Health insurance guide for Electricians working internationally, covering electrical trade positions abroad, skilled trade careers, and global electrician opportunities.";
const headline = "Insurance for International Electricians";
const subheadline = "Coverage solutions for Electricians working abroad, installing electrical systems internationally, and pursuing careers across construction and industrial settings worldwide.";
const canonicalPath = "/guides/electrician-insurance";
const heroBackgroundImage = "/images/guides/electrician-insurance-hero.png";

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', label: 'Overview' },
  { id: 'coverage-needs', label: 'Coverage Needs' },
  { id: 'work-settings', label: 'Work Settings' },
  { id: 'credentials', label: 'Credentials' },
  { id: 'occupational-health', label: 'Occupational Health' },
  { id: 'work-demands', label: 'Work Demands' },
  { id: 'career-considerations', label: 'Career Considerations' },
  { id: 'faqs', label: 'FAQs' },
  { id: 'next-steps', label: 'Next Steps' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title={title}
  description={description}
  headline={headline}
  subheadline={subheadline}
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  heroBackgroundImage={heroBackgroundImage}
  tocItems={tocItems}
>
  <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

    <section id="overview">
      <h2>International Electrician Careers</h2>
      <p>
        Electricians install, maintain, and repair electrical systems—wiring, lighting, controls, and power distribution. International electrical work offers opportunities to work on major construction projects, industrial facilities, and infrastructure developments across the globe.
      </p>
      <p>
        International electrician opportunities exist through international construction companies, offshore energy operations, industrial facilities, and countries actively recruiting skilled electrical tradespeople.
      </p>
      <p>
        This guide addresses insurance considerations for Electricians working abroad across construction and industrial settings worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="coverage-needs">
      <h2>Coverage Needs for Electricians</h2>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={[
          { key: 'need', header: 'Coverage Need' },
          { key: 'why', header: 'Why It Matters' },
          { key: 'typical', header: 'Coverage Situation?' },
        ]}
        rows={[
          { need: 'General health coverage', why: 'Professional health maintenance', typical: 'Usually employer-provided' },
          { need: 'Occupational injury', why: 'Electrical and physical hazards', typical: 'Essential for role' },
          { need: 'Emergency coverage', why: 'Electrical accident risk', typical: 'Essential for role' },
          { need: 'Ergonomic coverage', why: 'Physical work demands', typical: 'Important for role' },
          { need: 'Eye coverage', why: 'Arc flash and debris exposure', typical: 'Consider including' },
          { need: 'Travel coverage', why: 'Project-based assignments', typical: 'Often essential' },
        ]}
      />

      <h3>Electrical Hazards</h3>
      <p>
        Working with electricity involves inherent risks—electrical shock, arc flash, burns, and falls from heights. Even experienced electricians face these hazards daily. International work may involve unfamiliar systems, different voltage standards, and varying safety cultures.
      </p>
      <p>
        Comprehensive occupational injury and emergency coverage addresses the real risks of electrical work.
      </p>

      <h3>Physical Demands</h3>
      <p>
        Electrical work is physically demanding—working in confined spaces, climbing ladders, pulling wire, and working in awkward positions. These physical demands create musculoskeletal strain over time. Ergonomic coverage supports long-term career sustainability.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-settings">
      <h2>Coverage by Work Setting</h2>

      <h3>Construction</h3>
      <p>
        Major construction projects. Construction company benefits. Project-based work. Construction offers variety.
      </p>

      <h3>Industrial</h3>
      <p>
        Manufacturing or processing facility. Industrial employer benefits. Maintenance focus. Industrial offers stability.
      </p>

      <h3>Offshore</h3>
      <p>
        Oil rig or offshore platform. Comprehensive offshore benefits. Rotational schedule. Offshore offers compensation.
      </p>

      <h3>Infrastructure</h3>
      <p>
        Power generation or transmission. Utility or contractor benefits. Critical systems. Infrastructure offers importance.
      </p>

      <h3>Residential</h3>
      <p>
        Residential electrical work. Contractor benefits vary. Home construction. Residential offers community.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Coverage for Electricians"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Electricians working abroad across construction and industrial settings worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Electrician Plans"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

    <section id="credentials">
      <h2>Credentials and Professional Recognition</h2>

      <h3>Electrical License</h3>
      <p>
        Journeyman or master electrician license. Trade certification. Jurisdictional requirements. License often required.
      </p>

      <h3>Apprenticeship</h3>
      <p>
        Completed apprenticeship program. Trade training. Practical experience. Apprenticeship demonstrates competence.
      </p>

      <h3>Specialty Certifications</h3>
      <p>
        High voltage, PLC, industrial controls. Specialty training. Advanced credentials. Certifications add value.
      </p>

      <h3>Safety Training</h3>
      <p>
        OSHA, arc flash training. Safety certifications. Code compliance. Safety training required.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="occupational-health">
      <h2>Occupational Health Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Electrical Risk</h3>
      <p>
        Shock hazards. Arc flash exposure. Burns. Occupational injury coverage critical.
      </p>

      <h3>Physical Strain</h3>
      <p>
        Climbing. Confined spaces. Heavy lifting. Ergonomic coverage important.
      </p>

      <h3>Eye Hazards</h3>
      <p>
        Arc flash. Debris. Bright light. Eye coverage valuable.
      </p>

      <h3>Hearing</h3>
      <p>
        Industrial noise. Equipment operation. Construction sites. Hearing protection important.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-demands">
      <h2>Managing Work Demands</h2>

      <h3>Installation</h3>
      <p>
        New electrical systems. Wiring and distribution. Equipment connection. Installation builds infrastructure.
      </p>

      <h3>Maintenance</h3>
      <p>
        Preventive maintenance. Troubleshooting. Repair work. Maintenance ensures operation.
      </p>

      <h3>Code Compliance</h3>
      <p>
        Electrical code adherence. Inspection preparation. Safety standards. Compliance protects safety.
      </p>

      <h3>Documentation</h3>
      <p>
        Work records. As-built drawings. Test documentation. Documentation enables maintenance.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="career-considerations">
      <h2>Career Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Strong Demand</h3>
      <p>
        Electrical infrastructure expanding. Skilled trades shortage. Renewable energy growth. Demand excellent.
      </p>

      <h3>Career Paths</h3>
      <p>
        Master Electrician. Electrical Contractor. Supervisor. Inspector. Multiple paths available.
      </p>

      <h3>Credential Portability</h3>
      <p>
        Electrical skills universal. Licensing specific. Systems similar globally. Core skills portable.
      </p>

      <h3>Field Evolution</h3>
      <p>
        Renewable energy. Smart systems. EV infrastructure. Field evolving rapidly.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="faqs">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">I'm an electrician considering international work. What should I know?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Construction and industrial employers provide benefits. Licensing varies. Skills transfer. Safety culture differs.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do employers provide international coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Major employers yes. Offshore comprehensive. Construction contractors vary. Verify occupational coverage.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Are electrical hazards a significant concern?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Yes for electricians. Occupational risk real. Safety training critical. Injury coverage essential.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do electrical credentials transfer internationally?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Skills transfer well. Licensing specific. Code systems differ. Core competence portable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is offshore work different?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Rotational schedule. Comprehensive benefits. Higher compensation. Remote environment.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What's the career outlook?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Skilled trades shortage. Infrastructure investment. Electrification growth. Outlook excellent.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="next-steps">
      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <p>
        Start by evaluating employer benefits packages. Prioritize occupational injury coverage for electrical hazards. Ensure ergonomic support for physical demands. Verify emergency coverage for accident risk.
      </p>
      <p>
        Electricians power the world. Your coverage should support electrical careers—addressing occupational and physical demands, covering health maintenance, and protecting you across electrical work worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Protect Your Electrical Career"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Electricians working abroad across construction and industrial settings worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

  </article>
</PageShell>
